<html lang="en" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Pixel Mapper</title>
    <style type="text/css">
        body {
            background: #C0C0C0;
        }

        h1 {
            padding-bottom: 5px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid black;
        }

        h2, .h1 {
            margin-left: 15px;
        }

        h3, .h2 {
            margin-left: 30px;
        }

        h4, .h3 {
            margin-left: 45px;
        }

        h5, .h4 {
            margin-left: 60px;
        }

        img {
            width: 90%;
            border: 1px solid black;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }

        div#footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 5px;
            border-top: 1px solid black;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="wrapper">
        <h1>Pixel Mapper</h1>
        <div>
            <h2>About</h2>
            <p class="h2">
                Pixel Mapper allows one to preview what an image would look like through a defined filter and be able to export it into a non standard format.<br />
                <img alt="MainScreen" src="images/MainScreen.jpg" />
            </p>
            <h2><a href="download.html">Download</a></h2>
            <p class="h2">
                Application automatically checks once per month for any updates.
            </p>
            <h2>Profiles Included</h2>
            <h3>Conversion</h3>
            <h4>DMD64</h4>
            <p class="h4">
                64 Color display consisting of 4 shades per color channel (R,G,B).<br />
                Preview set up to convert input image into a 128 pixels wide by 32 pixel high render.<br />
                Brightness/Contrast : Alters image brightess and now defined one pixel is next to another.<br />
                <img alt="DMD64" src="images/BrightnessContrast.jpg" />
            </p>
            <h4>DMD Classic</h4>
            <p class="h4">
                One Color DMD display consisting of 4 shades of one color.<br />
                Preview set up to convert input image into a 128 pixels wide by 32 pixel high render.<br />
                Brightness/Contrast : Alters image brightess and now defined one pixel is next to another.<br />
                R/G/B : Shows how the weighted average grayscale image would look on a one color DMD.<br />
                <img alt="DMDClassic" src="images/DMDClassic.jpg" />
            </p>
            <h3>Output</h3>
            <h4>Matrix64</h4>
            <p class="h4">
                64 Color display where each pixel is stored as hex, binary 0b00BBGGRR, in a matrix like format.<br />
                ex: {Frame},{Frame}... where "Frame" = {Row},{Row}... where "Row" = {pixel, pixel...}
            </p>
            <h4>DMD Byte Packed Stream</h4>
            <p class="h4">
                Packs four pixels into one byte using the logic (0b11223344) where the width must be a multiple of 4
            </p>
        </div>
        <div id="footer">
            Copyright: RPGCor | Ryan Gau | 2015 - Current
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>